text:
Duck breast was still moist and tender. Sauce smoothered over the duck tasted too heavy on fermented bean paste for my liking. Cantonese style au jus much preferred.

Otherwise, pretty ordinary.
Roast duck is deboned. Roast pork had good meat and fat ratio, crispy skin. Stall provides soup for free!
Once again their roast meat never disappoints me !! Just come and try !!

Understand that they were previously located at Tanjong Pagar Realty Food House, and used to attract long queues during lunch time. Tried the charsiew, siobak and duck rice today and must say that itâ€™s very good. The sauce is sweet but not cloying, the meat is very tender.
